laboratory_examinations.findings: Post-treatment AFP level was 1.3 ng/ml (normal <7.5 ng/ml).
Pretreatment AFP level was not obtained; however, post-treatment AFP level was 1 ng/ml.
Normal AFP level was recorded (1 ng/ml) post-treatment, although positive for AFP immunostaining pre-treatment.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Significant reduction of tumor volume after multimodality therapy accounted for discordance between AFP expression in pretreatment tumor tissue and normal post-treatment serum AFP level.
